Subject: [PATCH] Add real Terms of Service and Privacy Policy pages
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Register's Terms checkbox (already required at signup) linked to
dead <span> text with no actual page behind it. Sign-in had no
Terms/Privacy mention at all. The landing page footer had two sets
of dead '#' links for Privacy/Terms.

- app/terms/page.tsx: new Terms of Service page. Includes two
  prominent, boxed disclaimer sections as specifically requested:
  (1) all cost figures (blueprint estimates, multi-cloud comparison,
  Brownfield cost-before/after, cost waste) are static ballpark
  estimates from standard on-demand reference pricing, NOT live
  cloud-provider pricing, and must be independently verified before
  any financial decision; (2) generated Terraform/IaC, security
  findings, and migration plans are provided as-is and must be
  independently reviewed by qualified engineers before being
  deployed or acted on in any live environment.
- app/privacy/page.tsx: new Privacy Policy — data collected,
  Supabase storage/RLS, Anthropic as AI subprocessor, GDPR rights,
  retention, cookies, contact.
- app/register/page.tsx: Terms of Service / Privacy Policy text in
  the existing (already-required) checkbox now links to the real
  pages, opened in a new tab so the in-progress form isn't lost.
- app/signin/page.tsx: added an informational Terms/Privacy line
  with real links. Not a mandatory checkbox — re-forcing consent on
  every login is atypical UX for users who already agreed once at
  signup; this can be changed to a hard requirement if preferred.
- public/landing.html: footer's two dead '#' Privacy/Terms link
  pairs now point to /privacy and /terms.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, next build succeeds (22/22 pages,
new /terms and /privacy routes confirmed in route table), no new
lint issues (the one warning in signin/page.tsx is pre-existing
and unrelated to this diff).
